{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/build-a-professional-network","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"ad3d8c60-ea7a-5536-b001-dbaf00a349da","name":"build-a-professional-network","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/build-a-professional-network.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/1Zr7VK4OehJ54tMZlCSG7s/d5c12ad571003c9c6aec5a90fa9cb8e8/2017-11-05-build-a-professional-network.jpg?w=4288&h=2848","alt":"Flowers"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Since I just was interviewed about this topic, I'll try to write down some of my\nrecommendations on how to build a professional network if you are early in your\ncareer and how to progress from there. Actually I am practicing all of these\nactions even today."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I'll focus on building a network to other professionals in your industry, since\nthis will enable you to learn about new technologies, improve you skills based\non experiences they are sharing and ask for support, find mentors and later on\njobs and hires."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In my experience the tech scene is especially good approachable on "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Twitter"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nI find myself "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"following a lot developers"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twitter.com/following","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" there\nand this way I get daily access to what is going on tech-wise. The real-time\ncharacter of the network has it's advantages: you can easily interact on a given\ntopic but it rarely happens that someone resurrects a old post. It's very easy\nto approach someone with a question there, and they usually will answer right\naway."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"But make now mistake, "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"following"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" someone on Twitter is a one-way street, to\nbuild a network you have to "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"share something"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" so people can become aware of\nyou. And since connections are built on trust, it means you have to expose\nyourself to some degree. And this exposure needs to happen in the physical\nworld, only there will you be able to build connections that support exchange\nabout personal and confidential matters which is the basis for finding good\nadvisors and mentors."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The first step is to go to local meetups. Do not fear to go there as a\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"beginner"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", the first step to learning something is to embrace the unknown. It's\na great opportunity to learn to know new people and find out who you would be\ninterested to talk to. You will find that approaching someone there is a lot\neasier compared to a contacting them only e.g. through LinkedIn. Since you are\nboth part of the same interest group, and you took the time to be present at the\nmeetup will give you already some credibility. Also, it's harder to turn down\nsomeone who is approaching you face to face."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Early in your career you should develop the confidence to "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"give your first\ntalk"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". Watch other speakers and try to find someone with experience as a\nspeaker to give you feedback on your talk. Most meetups will be happy to host a\nbeginner talk,\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"since they always provide really valuable input"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://coderbyheart.com/bring-your-inexperience-to-a-conference/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nGiving talks will put you in the spotlight‚Äîdoing it at a small meetup where you\nknow people can be even more uncomfortable compared to a huge conference‚Äîbut it\nalso gives you a lot of visibility. I can highly recommend\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"the software crafter communities"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://softwarecrafters.org/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" around the\nworld as a very inclusive and beginner-friendly community of professionals."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Every talk creates the opportunity to reuse the content in multiple ways. You\ncan use it to share your findings on your blog, but even better: submit it to a\nconference."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The next step of building a valuable network is to "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"attend conferences"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". At\nconferences you will be able connect with a great variety of people. Those that\nshare the same problems as you do and other beginners which will be a great\nresource when learning a new topic since you can exchange about your findings\nand problems. Since last year, it became common to connect through a Slack\ninstance for that conference. Here you can also easily approach speakers, with\nyour questions or on general to just give them feedback on their talk. In both\ncase they will usually be very open and happy to help you. It's a good idea to\ncheck out a conference schedule beforehand and follow the speakers on Twitter,\ndoing that you can start building a connection to them even before the event."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You should "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"submit your beginner talk"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" to conferences, because giving a talk\nwill teach you so many great things that improve your skills on many levels. You\ncan find conferences that accept proposals (Call for Papers, or "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"CfP"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" for short)\non "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"papercall.io"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.papercall.io/events","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" or through\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"lanyrd"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://lanyrd.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". Karolina has a great post on\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"How to write a successful conference proposal"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://medium.com/@fox/how-to-write-a-successful-conference-proposal-4461509d3e32","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nBecoming a speaker on a conference will give you a lot of visibility and\nprovides a great opportunity to meet other industry experts on eye-level."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Build a professional network","subtitle":"Markus, How do I ...","noheadline":null,"date":"2017-11-05T14:00+01:00","abstract":"My recommendations on how to build a professional network if you are early in your career.","lang":null},"headings":[]}},"Footer":{"id":"cfe5b9e2-511c-5615-992a-dab82e1f8ed7","name":"Footer","relativeDirectory":"","relativePath":"Footer.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nordic Semiconductor"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://nordicsemi.